body:
The `test/Conversion/ExportVerilog/disallow-local-vars.mlir` testcase when run with  `circt-opt --lowering-options=disallowLocalVariables` produces some silly verilog with extra copies:

```
module side_effect_expr(
...
  output a, a2);

  reg _T_0;

  wire _T = INLINE_OK;
  wire _T_1 = _T_0;  
...

module EmittedDespiteDisallowed( 
  input clock, reset);

  reg       tick_value_2;
  reg       counter_value;
  reg [1:0] _T;

  wire [1:0] _T_0 = _T;
  wire _T_1 = _T_0[0];
  wire _T_2 = _T_0[1]; 
 ```

The _T_1 wire in the first example and the _T_0 wire in the second example are obviously unnecessary.
